# Capstone: SaaS Marketing Site

Your first capstone is a complete, multi-section marketing site — the kind that converts. It exercises
the full first half of the course (layout, responsive, type, color, motion) on top of your design
system.

<ProjectBrief
	title="Build a converting SaaS marketing site"
	time="2–4 hours"
	goal="Build a polished, responsive, themeable marketing site: sticky nav, hero, logo cloud, feature grid, testimonial, pricing, FAQ (accordion), and footer — all on semantic tokens, dark-mode ready, accessible, and animated tastefully."
	requirements={[
		'Sticky nav with mobile menu and a clear primary CTA',
		'Hero with responsive headline, subcopy, dual CTAs, and a gradient accent',
		'Feature grid using container queries so it works in any column',
		'Pricing section reusing your Module 2 pricing-card patterns',
		'FAQ built on your accordion (or a headless library), fully accessible',
		'Light/dark themes via semantic tokens; visible focus everywhere',
		'Tasteful motion (hover lifts, reveal-on-scroll) honouring reduced-motion'
	]}
	stretch={[
		'Add a second brand via data-brand to prove the token system',
		'Prerender it (prerender = true) for instant loads',
		'Add a Lighthouse/perf budget check in CI'
	]}
/>

