## Architecture guidance

- **Compose, don't repeat:** each section is a Svelte component; the page assembles them.
- **Semantics only:** sections consume `accent`, `ink`, `surface` — never raw colours — so the second
  brand is a one-line proof.
- **Container queries** for feature/pricing grids so sections drop into any layout.
- **Motion budget:** one reveal style, one hover lift, reused — calm, not carnival.

<Callout type="insight" title="A marketing site is judged in seconds — make the fundamentals flawless">

Conversion lives in the fundamentals you've drilled: a single obvious CTA per section, restrained
palette, confident type hierarchy, generous whitespace, fast load, and motion that guides rather than
distracts. There's nothing exotic here — and that's the mark of mastery. When you can produce a site
this polished from your own system, reusing patterns from across the course, you've proven the first
half cold. Treat the visual restraint as the hard part, because it is.

</Callout>

## Acceptance criteria

- Passes `pnpm check`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm build` with prerendering.
- Fully responsive from 320px up; keyboard-navigable; visible focus throughout.
- Light and dark themes both contrast-safe; a second brand swappable via one attribute.
- No raw colours in section components — semantic tokens only.
